Q Hi all, i'm encountering the problem with deploying develop branch to my Siren env, the console output shows as below FATAL: command execution failed hudson.AbortException: Ansible playbook execution failed at org.jenkinsci.plugins.ansible.AnsiblePlaybookBuilder.perform(AnsiblePlaybookBuilder.java:226) at org.jenkinsci.plugins.ansible.AnsiblePlaybookBuilder.perform(AnsiblePlaybookBuilder.java:199) at hudson.tasks.BuildStepCompatibilityLayer.perform(BuildStepCompatibilityLayer.java:78) at hudson.tasks.BuildStepMonitor$1.perform(BuildStepMonitor.java:20) at hudson.model.AbstractBuild$AbstractBuildExecution.perform(AbstractBuild.java:779) at hudson.model.Build$BuildExecution.build(Build.java:206) at hudson.model.Build$BuildExecution.doRun(Build.java:163) at hudson.model.AbstractBuild$AbstractBuildExecution.run(AbstractBuild.java:534) at hudson.model.Run.execute(Run.java:1728) at hudson.model.FreeStyleBuild.run(FreeStyleBuild.java:43) at hudson.model.ResourceController.execute(ResourceController.java:98) at hudson.model.Executor.run(Executor.java:405) ERROR: Ansible playbook execution failed Finished: FAILURE
A Reason is Pegasus added "absolute-device-unenroll-webservice" to list of war_debians to be deployed into team environment. This web service is not merged into develop, thus your branch doesn't have this module. I guess other teams will face same problem when building team environment. I will comment out this module to avoid this problem
